Title: Point-like Instantons on K3 Orbifolds
Authors: Paul S. Aspinwall and David R. Morrison
Comments: 35 pages, many embedded figures. Caveat added concerning result 4
Report-no: RU-97-29 IASSNS-HEP-97/46
Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys. B503 (1997) 533-564
\\
  The map between the moduli space of F-theory (or type II string)
compactifications and heterotic string compactifications can be considerably
simplified by using "stable degenerations". We discuss how this method applies
to both the E8 x E8 and the Spin(32)/Z2 heterotic string. As a simple
application of this method we derive some basic properties of the
nonperturbative physics of collections of E8 or Spin(32)/Z2 point-like
instantons sitting at A-D-E singularities on a K3 surface.
